<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-faqs-on-person-schema">FAQs on Person Schema</h2>



<div data-schema-only="false" class="wp-block-aioseo-faq" id="aioseo-is-person-schema-restricted-to-real-vs-fictional-characters"><h3 class="aioseo-faq-block-question">Is person schema restricted to real vs. fictional characters?</h3><div class="aioseo-faq-block-answer">
<p>No, person schema can be used for real or fictional characters.</p>



<p>When adding person schema to fictional characters, you would fill out relevant fields for job, nationality, languages spoken, areas of expertise, who they’re related to, and so on.</p>



<p>In addition, person schema can be used for historical figures.</p>
</div></div>



<div data-schema-only="false" class="wp-block-aioseo-faq" id="aioseo-what-is-a-schema-generator"><h3 class="aioseo-faq-block-question">What is a schema generator?</h3><div class="aioseo-faq-block-answer">
<p>A schema generator, in the context of SEO plugins, is a tool that helps website owners or developers create structured data markup for their web pages.</p>



<p>An SEO plugin with a schema generator typically provides a user-friendly interface where you can input relevant information about your web page, such as:</p>



<ul>
<li>Page type (e.g., article, product, event, recipe)</li>



<li>Author information</li>



<li>Ratings and reviews</li>



<li>Product details (e.g., price, availability)</li>



<li>Event details (e.g., date, time, location)</li>
</ul>



<p>Once you input the necessary information, the schema generator creates the appropriate structured data markup, which is added to your page&#8217;s HTML code.</p>



<p>Popular SEO plugins like All in One SEO offer built-in schema generators that support various schema types and help users implement structured data markup without needing to code.</p>
</div></div>



